$NetBSD: TODO,v 1.7989 2009/03/21 21:37:09 snj Exp $

Suggested new packages
======================

	any unresolved PRs (if you have commit access)
	http://www.netbsd.org/Gnats/category/pkg.html

	any complete, polished packages in pkgsrc-wip (ditto)
	http://pkgsrc-wip.sourceforge.net/

	bacula-rescue
	Scripts used to help create rescue boot cd's for bare metal
	restores with bacula.  Scripts exist for linux, solaris, and
	FreeBSD.  Hopefully the FreeBSD one could be adapted to create
	a NetBSD one or perhaps it could be turned into a *BSD script.
	http://www.bacula.org/

	resin
	Fast JSP server. (I will import this when we have a native
	Java 2 -- it can't be built with our native jdk. [jwise])
	http://www.caucho.com/products/resin/index.xtp

	SquirrelMail plugins
	SquirrelMail has a plugin feature and several plugins exist.
	(See mail/sq-squirrelspell for an example.)
	http://www.squirrelmail.org/index.php3?page=15

	p5-CGI-AppToolkit-0.051
	Perl CGI application toolkit
	${MASTER_SITE_PERL_CPAN:=CGI/}

	info2man
	http://freshmeat.net/projects/info2man/
	requires perl, provides info2man and info2pod

	moji
	http://moji.mozdev.org/
	Mozilla Firefox extension which helps you learn Japanese

	joyce
	http://www.seasip.demon.co.uk/Unix/Joyce/index.html
	Amstrad PCW emulator

	wxmozilla
	http://wxmozilla.sourceforge.net/
	Mozilla using the wxWidgets toolkit.

	SlimServer
	http://www.slimdevices.com/pi_features.html
	Slim Devices audio streaming server

	Helix Player
	http://player.helixcommunity.org/2004/downloads/
	RealNetwork's open source audio/video player

	Attal: Lords of Doom
	http://www.attal-thegame.org/
	Turn based strategy game

	Sphinx-4
	http://cmusphinx.sourceforge.net/sphinx4/
	Speaker-independent, continuous speech recognition system.

	doxywizard
	QT-based wizard for doxygen documentation generator.
	See pkgsrc/devel/doxygen

	tkfontsel
	http://ftp.sunet.se/pub/lang/tcl/sorted/graphics/tkfontsel/
	http://ftp.se.kde.org/pub/lang/tcl/sorted/packages-7.6/graphics/tkfontsel/
	Simple Tk font browser.

	xftlsfonts
	FreeType font list displayer.

	choosefont
	http://choosefont.sourceforge.net/
	Utility for browsing, previewing and selecting a X11 font.

	logrider
	http://ilya-evseev.narod.ru/posix/logrider/
	Scan system logs for alert/hacking signatures based on set
	of static filters.

	ardour
	http://ardour.org/
	Digital audio workstation with plugins, professional mixer,
	multichannel recording, and more.

	libdisassemble
	http://www.immunitysec.com/resources-freesoftware.shtml
	http://lwn.net/Articles/98988/?format=printable
	Python library that will disassemble X86.

	pdftk
	http://www.accesspdf.com/pdftk/
	PDF manipulation tool for merging, splitting, decrypting,
	encrypting, and more.
	[use Java classes in C++ program]

	guipdftk
	http://de.geocities.com/dpaehl2004/guipdftk/
	GUI for Pdftk for PDF manipulation

	grip
	http://nostatic.org/grip/
	cd-player and cd-ripper for the Gnome desktop

	wired
	http://bloodshed.net/wired/
	Professional music production and creation software

	ices-mp3-v2
	http://www.icecast.org/ices.php
	Major version 2 of ices-mp3
	Maintainer reply:
	    The ices-mp3 package is for ices0.  There is no MP3 support
	    in ices2.  This is why I called the package "ices-mp3" when
	    I initially created it.  (kim@)

	cricket 1.0.5
	http://cricket.sourceforge.net
	Monitoring & graphing system based on RRDtool

	Webware for Python
	http://www.webwareforpython.org/
	Suite of software components for developing object-oriented,
	web-based applications.

	TROPHY
	http://trophy.sourceforge.net/
	A 2D car racing action game with untypical racing game features
	such as shooting at other players.

	The Open Racing Car Simulator [pkgsrc-wip]
	http://torcs.sf.net/
	TORCS is a 3D racing cars simulator using OpenGL. The goal
	is to have programmed robots drivers racing against each
	others.  You can also drive yourself with either a wheel or
	keyboard or mouse.

	CarWorld driving simulator
	http://carworld.sourceforge.net/
	A small driving simulator/demo.

	Road Fighter remake
	http://www.braingames.getput.com/roadf/
	Unofficial remake of Konami's ROAD FIGHTER which was
	originally released in 1985 for the MSX home computer
	systems.  In Road Fighter you drive a car in a death
	race between you and a group of crazy  drivers.

	XRally
	http://www.linuxgames.com/xrally/
	Clone of the classic Rally X arcade game using basic Xlib
	and Xpm. You control a blue (good) car, that has to collect
	yellow flags around a maze-like map, while avoiding the
	red (bad) cars.

	Postoffice
	http://www.pell.portland.or.us/~orc/Code/postoffice/index.html
	Simple SMTP mail server and client.

	oKle
	http://okle.sourceforge.net/
	KDE frontend to the Ogle DVD player.

	LabelNation
	http://www.red-bean.com/labelnation/
	Command-line label, business card printing program.

	Enigmail
	http://enigmail.mozdev.org/
	GnuPG extension for the Mozilla/Thunderbird mail client

	VirtualBox
	http://www.virtualbox.org/
	Fast x86 emulator

	qphotosort
	http://pintant.cat/qphotosort
	rename photos by date to support merged albums from different sources

	TinySNMP
	http://oasis.frogfoot.net/code/tinysnmp/
	Fast lightweight SNMPv1 daemon

	BSNMP
	http://oasis.frogfoot.net/code/tinysnmp/
	Mini SNMP daemon

	TrueCrypt
	http://www.truecrypt.org/
	Hard drive encryption software

	ReportMagic
	http://www.reportmagic.org/
	Builds nice looking statistics reports for output from www/analog

	mime-support [pkg/28529]
	Support commands for manipulating files using MIME and mailcap

	Compiler of the AGFL formalis [pkg/28946]
	formalism for the syntactic description of Natural Languages

	DCC [pkg/29619]
	http://www.rhyolite.com/anti-spam/dcc/
	Distributed Checksum Clearinghouse [pkg/29619]

	Azureus [pkg/29976, pkg/30103, pkgsrc-wip]
	http://azureus.sourceforge.net/
	Bittorrent client written in java

	Webfwlog Firewall Log Analyzer [pkg/30110]
	http://www.webfwlog.net/
	Web-Based Firewall Log Analysis and Reporting
	
	FreeVRRPd [pkg/30113]
	VRRP (Virtual Router Redundancy Protocol) implementation daemon

	Algol 68 Genie [pkg/30695]
	http://www.xs4all.nl/~jmvdveer/algol.html
	Algol 68 interpreter

	SystemC class library [pkg/30707]
	http://www.systemc.org/
	SystemC is a C++ class collection for modelling systems.

	crm114 [pkg/31969]
	http://crm114.sourceforge.net/
	Controllable Regex Mutilator

	sysjail [pkg/34123, pkgsrc-wip]
	http://sysjail.bsd.lv/
	userland virtualisation system

	Raster3D [pkg/34225]
	http://skuld.bmsc.washington.edu/raster3d/

	libpcapnav [pkg/34473]
	http://netdude.sourceforge.net/
	Wrapper library that allows navigation in tcpdump traces

	libnetdude [pkg/34473]
	http://netdude.sourceforge.net/
	Library for manipulating libpcap/tcpdump trace files

	netdude [pkg/34473]
	http://netdude.sourceforge.net/
	NETwork DUmp data Displayer and Editor for tcpdump tracefiles

	INADYN [pkg/34502]
	INADYN is a free DynDNS client.

	Fenix Project [pkg/35346]
	http://fenix.divsite.net
	
	*BSD Usage Statistics [pkg/35365]
	http://www.bsdstats.org/
	Report machine statistics to the BSDstats Project

	Skins for XMMS [pkg/35666]
	http://www.xmms.org/skins.php

	Berkeley automounter suite of utilities [pkg/35668]
	http://www.am-utils.org/

	Javascript major mode for Emacs [pkg/35669]
	http://www.brgeight.se/

	THEAMA [pkg/35896]
	http://sourceforge.net/projects/theama
	curses-based version of the famous HangMan game.

	sharatype [pkg/36217]
	http://ftp.45.free.net/pub/fonts/type1/
	Cyrillic fonts for a2ps (a part of sharatype project)

	xmms-cdread [pkg/36220]
	ftp://mud.stack.nl/pub/OuterSpace/willem/
	XMMS input plugin that reads audio data from CDs

	ioquake3 [pkg/36365, pkg/36366, pkg/36367]

	OTR localhost AIM proxy [pkg/37397]
	http://www.cypherpunks.ca/otr/
	Off-the-Record Messaging Proxy

	M+ FONTS [pkg/37614]
	http://mplus-fonts.sourceforge.jp/
	Small and neat Japanese bitmap fonts

	tkimg [pkg/38026]
	http://tkimg.sourceforge.net/
	Add support for several image formats to Tk

	tktable [pkg/38027]
	http://tktable.sourceforge.net/
	Grid/table/spreadsheet like widget for Tk

	tDOM [pkg/38028]
	http://www.tdom.org/
	C based XML extension for Tcl

	xine-plugin [pkg/38159]
	http://xinehq.de/
	Plugin for www/firefox for using multimedia/xine-lib

	flyback [pkgsrc-wip]
	http://code.google.com/p/flyback/
	Backup software inspired by Apple's Time Machine

	filezilla client
	http://filezilla-project.org
	Featureful FTP, FTPS and SFTP client	

	SpiralSynthModular (spiralmodular)
	http://www.pawfal.org/Software/SSM/
	Obsoletes audio/spiralloops and audio/spiralsynth, which are
	no longer supported.

	STklos
	http://www.stklos.org/
	Scheme system. "STklos is the next generation of STklos using
	GTK," obsoletes lang/STk.

	sage
	http://www.sagemath.org/
	Open-source alternative to Magma, Maple, Mathematica, Matlab.

